e element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Princess Orlagg O'Brien Thomond was born about 1399, in Bunratty Castle, County Clare, Ireland. She married Lawrence The Barry Roe Barry about 1420, in Bunratty Castle, County Clare, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1463, in Barryroe, County Cork, Ireland, at the age of 65."},"et":{"abt 1399–1463":"umbes 1399–1463","1395–1444":"1395–1444","1429–Male":"1429–Surnud","1399–1463":"1399–1463","1444":"1444","1399":"1399","1463":"1463","1395":"1395","1429":"1429","abt 1420":"umbes 1420","abt 1399":"umbes 1399","Barry Roe, Cork, Ireland":"Barryroe, County Cork, Iirimaa","Bunratty Castle, Connaught, Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland":"Bunratty Castle, County Clare, Iirimaa"},